All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
AddMetadataPanel
This panel allows the user to enter the Maze name and author name.
ExportDialog
Exports selected mazes with or without the solution line in the directory specified by the user
GUIFrame
The top-level container of the application.
ImagePropertiesPanel
Side panel controlling the properties for Logo and maze start/end images.
LandingControlPanel
Container for the options to export selected mazes and create a new maze.
LandingPanel
Panel displayed on startup.
Maze
Logical representation of a maze.
MazeBrowserTable
Table to browse previously created mazes.
MazeCanvasPanel
Editing canvas containing the maze
MazeCellBorderPanel
Panel for the border between maze cells.
MazeCellInsidePanel
Contains the maze cell.
MazeDatabase
Class to communicate with the database to store and retrieve past mazes.
MazeDimensions
Container for holding information about the dimensions of a maze object
MazeEntryExitPoint
Maze entry or exit point which can be either just a wall opening or a start/end image
MazeExportHandler
Handles exporting mazes as an image file
MazeGenerationPanel
Panel that contains the canvas for editing the maze
MazeGrid
Panel to contain the maze grid.
MazeImage
Interface for images placed on the maze
MazeItem
Interface for maze items, such as logos, cells, maze starts/ends
MazeLayout
Container for storing the maze layout
MazeLayoutGenerator
Handles the automatic generation of maze layouts
MazeLocation
Describes any location on the maze
MazeLogo
Specifies properties of MazeLogos on the maze grid
MazeMetadata
Container for maze metadata
MazePropertiesPanel
Side panel controlling the properties for the maze
MazeStartEndImage
Specifies the properties of start/end images on the maze canvas
MouseAdapter
Empty MouseListener implementation that allows to only implement specific classes in inheriting classes
Program
Entry point to the application.
ProgressControlPanel
 
PropertiesPanel
Panel displayed on east Maze Generation panel.
